{"session_id":"svc-1778132790327333058","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T05:46:30.376206674Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-a1ae37ff-20260507T054628-fc523f66","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-a1ae37ff\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: scope mechanical --no-verify commits (CommitTracker, AutoCommit) so leftover staged paths can\u0026#39;t piggy-back\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;During `ddx work` / `ddx agent execute-bead`, unrelated junk gets swept into mechanical \u0026#34;tracker\u0026#34; commits even though hooks correctly reject it on the visible commit path. Concrete instance: commit a2b37a405 (\u0026#34;chore: update tracker (execute-bead 20260507T043117)\u0026#34;) committed a 12MB `.ddx/backups/beads-20260507T042910.jsonl` plus ~60 other unrelated paths, under a message that\u0026#39;s supposed to mean \u0026#34;I touched .ddx/beads.jsonl and nothing else.\u0026#34;\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;Two unscoped --no-verify commit sites:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1239-1252 (CommitTracker):\u0026#xA;    git add .ddx/beads.jsonl\u0026#xA;    git commit --no-verify -m msg\u0026#xA;  The git commit is unscoped — it commits everything currently in the index, not just the staged tracker file.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/git/autocommit.go:67-75 (AutoCommit):\u0026#xA;    git add \u0026lt;basename\u0026gt;\u0026#xA;    git commit --no-verify -m message\u0026#xA;  Same shape. Used by bead create/claim/update/close/migrate/archive.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Leak chain: pre-checkpoint SynthesizeCommit(projectRoot, ...) at execute_bead.go:734 runs `git add -A .` in the parent repo. If lefthook (e.g. large-files) rejects, the index stays populated. The next CommitTracker or AutoCommit runs `git commit --no-verify`, bypassing hooks and committing the leftover index wholesale.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`--no-verify` is intentional for mechanical commits (avoids running go test on every bead status change). Scoping is what\u0026#39;s missing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1249 → `git commit --no-verify --only -- .ddx/beads.jsonl -m msg`. `--only -- \u0026lt;path\u0026gt;` commits that path only and leaves the rest of the index untouched.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/git/autocommit.go:73 → `git commit --no-verify --only -- \u0026lt;basename\u0026gt; -m message`.\u0026#xA;- The pre-stage `git add` lines may stay (defense in depth) or be dropped (`--only` stages from working tree implicitly). Either is fine; do not remove the byte-identical-to-HEAD bail at execute_bead.go:1246.\u0026#xA;- Add regression tests (see AC).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Removing the existing 12MB blob from git history (force-push decision; out of band).\u0026#xA;- .gitignore entry for .ddx/backups/ (defense-in-depth, may be addressed separately; the invariant being fixed here must not depend on which directories are gitignored).\u0026#xA;- Architectural change to run tracker writes inside the worker worktree (epic-shaped; see INTERSECTIONS).\u0026#xA;- SynthesizeCommit\u0026#39;s `git add -A` semantics (intentionally broad, gated by hooks; correct as-is).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;- ddx-55f05e07 (closed): \u0026#34;Keep execute-bead checkpoint bases free of unrelated DDx runtime churn\u0026#34; — same problem class for the checkpoint commit; did not cover --no-verify commits.\u0026#xA;- Architectural follow-up (separate bead, not this one): consider running tracker writes inside the worker worktree so the parent repo is never the commit context for ddx-internal mechanical commits — would make this whole class of leak structurally impossible.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go CommitTracker invokes `git commit --no-verify --only -- .ddx/beads.jsonl -m \u0026lt;msg\u0026gt;` (path-scoped). Verify by reading the file.\u0026#xA;2. cli/internal/git/autocommit.go AutoCommit invokes `git commit --no-verify --only -- \u0026lt;basename\u0026gt; -m \u0026lt;msg\u0026gt;`. Verify by reading the file.\u0026#xA;3. TestCommitTracker_IgnoresUnrelatedStagedPaths (new, cli/internal/agent/): set up a temp git repo with committed .ddx/beads.jsonl, modify it, then `git add` an unrelated 6MB file to the index, call CommitTracker, assert `git show --name-only HEAD` lists only `.ddx/beads.jsonl` AND the unrelated file is still listed by `git diff --cached --name-only`.\u0026#xA;4. TestAutoCommit_IgnoresUnrelatedStagedPaths (new, cli/internal/git/autocommit_test.go): same shape against AutoCommit(\u0026#34;…/beads.jsonl\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;beads\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;test op\u0026#34;, AutoCommit=\u0026#34;always\u0026#34;).\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/git/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:git, kind:bug, reliability, prevention, observed-failure\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-32b3008e\" base-rev=\"23be1edbd481e99c01c90096348662aa4fdec33b\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260507T054628-fc523f66","base_rev":"23be1edbd481e99c01c90096348662aa4fdec33b","bead_id":"ddx-a1ae37ff","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66","correlation_id":"ddx-a1ae37ff:20260507T054628-fc523f66","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260507T054628-fc523f66/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"8f6d3d108ff909a9866dbce621b2c363ad69fbc9b10555d9ad4eea5087ba7e99","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-f44d4e32","worker_id":""}}}
